      "rationale": "No formal use-error assessment was performed. Boundary conditions were peer-reviewed internally but no blind re-simulation or independent verification of model setup was conducted. Flagged as epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The constitutive model for hemolysis (power-law damage model) must be justified against alternative model forms with documented sensitivity analysis at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model was selected without formal comparison to alternative formulations (e.g., strain-based models, Bludszuweit model). A one-at-a-time sensitivity analysis on model constants was performed but did not include model-form uncertainty. At MRL 5, this represents a critical gap; achieved level is 2."
    },
    {
